                      h4 Summary
                .col-lg-8.col-md-8.col-sm-8.col-xs-8.bhoechie-tab
                  .bhoechie-tab-content.active
                    p Luca, a single parent with limited digital literacy skills and limited English skills, relies on the library for access to computers and the Internet. Today, she’s using the library to renew her unemployment insurance and food stamps, both of which ask her to provide sensitive information.
                  .bhoechie-tab-content
                    ol
                      li Cyberthieves could intercept her information and steal her identity, and siphon benefits away from her.
                      li Getting her identity back and correcting her records would cost thousands of dollars and many, many hours.
                      li Because Luca is not very familiar with internet technology, she’s doing little to protect herself.
                  .bhoechie-tab-content
                    p Make sure she’s visiting official unemployment insurance and food stamp websites--as opposed to fake ones--and that these sites are encrypted.
                  .bhoechie-tab-content
                    p She could also take steps to erase her browser history in order to ensure that no cyberthief could access her data by those means.
                  .bhoechie-tab-content
                    p Learning how to create strong passwords is essential to her safety.
                  .bhoechie-tab-content
                    p Finally, we recommend she makes sure to log off of the library computer terminals to ensure no one can access her accounts.
                  .bhoechie-tab-content
                    p Info to be protected
                    ul
                      li Personal information (e.g. Name, DOB, SSN)
                      li Children’s personal information
                      li Financial information
                      li Location Information
                    p Who is likely to access info against patron’s will?
                    ul
                      li Cyberthieves
                    p What patron is doing/should do to keep their info private?
                    ul
                      li Browse via HTTPS
                      li Clear browser history and cookies
                      li Log off library terminal
                      li Create strong passwords
